                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/315: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-20T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 20, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>344. Department’s 212 December 19, 1 p.m. Braden having repeated to me
                    Department’s 178, December 18, noon, I took occasion to discuss the matter with
                    Macedo Soares yesterday afternoon and he immediately instructed Rodriguez Alves
                    by telegraph in the sense desired. I so informed Braden yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
